{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Description\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A script for stretching MIDI events in the MIDI editor. The script can either stretch event positions (horizontally) or values (vertically), depending on the mouse position. The script only affects events in the MIDI editor lane that is under the mouse cursor. If snap to grid is enabled, the stretch position will snap to grid.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Instructions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To use, 1) Select the MIDI events to be stretched,\line 2) Position the mouse in the CC lane (or in the notes area or velocity lane in the case of notes) 3) To stretch the leftmost events (using the rightmost event as anchor), position the mouse to left of the events' time range.\line To stretch events on the right, position the mouse to the right of the events' time range. To stretch vertically, position mouse closer to the middle of the time range. 4) Press the shortcut key. 5) Move mouse left or right if stretching horizontally, or up or down if stretching vertically. 6) To exit, move mouse out of CC lane, or press shortcut key again.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 There are two ways in which this script can be run:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab First, the script can be linked to its own shortcut key.\par}
